STA36375 | Ethics of Data: Reproducibility, Replicability, and ResponsibilityThis Section Cancelled | https://enr-apps.as.cmu.edu/open/SOC/SOCServlet/courseDetails?COURSE=36375&SEMESTER=F18 | description:As data set size and ease of collection grow, so does societys reliance on using statistical and machine learning methodology to extract information for the purposes of making decisions with far-reaching consequences.  However, of equal importance, so also grows the need to think carefully about how we use data and analytics tools and the potential impact that incorrect or ignored assumptions and choices can have.  In this seminar, we explore the ethics of data analysis including the notions of reproducibility, replicability, and responsible conduct of research.  There will be weekly readings, discussions, and/or analyses of case studies and related published research. Students must be at least at the sophomore level and have taken at least one statistics course.
