STA36401 | Modern Regression | https://enr-apps.as.cmu.edu/open/SOC/SOCServlet/courseDetails?COURSE=36401&SEMESTER=F18 | instructors:Lee, Ann prereq:(36226 or 36326 or 36625 or 36218) and (21240 or 21241) description:This course is an introduction to the real world of statistics and data analysis. We will explore real data sets, examine various models for the data, assess the validity of their assumptions, and determine which conclusions we can make (if any). Data analysis is a bit of an art; there may be several valid approaches. We will strongly emphasize the importance of critical thinking about the data and the question of interest. Our overall goal is to use a basic set of modeling tools to explore and analyze data and to present the results in a scientific report. A minimum grade of C in any one of the pre-requisites is required.  A grade of C is required to move on to 36-402 or any 36-46x course.
