STA36709 | Advanced Statistical Theory I | https://enr-apps.as.cmu.edu/open/SOC/SOCServlet/courseDetails?COURSE=36709&SEMESTER=S19 | instructors:Rinaldo, Alessandro prereq:36705 description:This is a core Ph.D. course in theoretical statistics. The class will cover a selection of modern topics in mathematical statistics, focussing on high-dimensional parametric models and non-parametric models. The main goal of the course is to provide the students with adequate theoretical background and mathematical tools to read and understand the current statistical literature on high-dimensional models. Topics will include: concentration inequalities, covariance estimation, principal component analysis, penalized linear regression, maximal inequalities for empirical processes, Rademacher and Gaussian complexities, non-parametric regression and minimax theory. This will be the first part of a two semester sequence.
